gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Thunder 134, Clippers 115
gameRecap.excerpt: The Thunder defeated the Clippers, 134-115. Shai Gilgeous-Alexander led Oklahoma City with 31 points, eight rebounds, four assists, and four steals as Chet Holmgren added 23 points (9-11 FG), six rebounds, and seven assists. James Harden (23 points, nine rebounds, six assists) and Paul George (22 points, four rebounds, four assists) led the Clippers as Russell Westbrook added 15 points and 13 rebounds in the loss. The Thunder win their third in a row, snap the Clippers 9-game win streak as they improve to 18-8 as the Clippers move to 17-11.
